description:
&lt;p&gt;We are currently recruiting for Biomedical Scientists to join our fast paced and dynamic Blood Sciences team. This role is part of a team which provides an efficient and effective service to two general hospitals (Southend University/Basildon and Thurrock University Hospitals) and local GP community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an important member of our team, you will be the fundamental principle of making a positive difference to our healthcare service and in return you will receive regular training and coaching to develop your skills and to support you in your working life. Ideally, we seek candidates who are passionate with good interpersonal skills and the drive to develop their career forward within our supportive environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You should be either registered with the Health &amp; Care Professions Council (HCPC) or have evidence of eligibility and have completed the IBMS registration portfolio/ equivalent. Please note that we will consider applications from candidates nearing completion of their pre-registration portfolio.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will be:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work across 3 different sites in a 24-7 work environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to work with a high degree of accuracy, numeracy, interpretive skills and good problem-solving skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Able to demonstrate a good knowledge and experience of industry standard laboratory information management systems and computer applications including Word, Excel, Power Point, Access and Statistical Packages.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is an excellent opportunity for a Biomedical Scientist who wants to develop their skills and experience in a state of the art laboratory&lt;/p&gt;
